data.title: Science - Elements & Metals
data.description: This game is based on General science - Elements and Metals.

levels.question: Brass gets discoloured in air because of the presence of which of the following gases in air?
levels.closingAnswer: Brass gets discoloured in air because of the presence of Hydrogen sulphide in air.

levels.question: Which of the following is a non metal that remains liquid at room temperature?
levels.closingAnswer: Bromine is a non metal that remains liquid at room temperature.

levels.question: Which of the following is used in pencils?
Which of the gas is not known as green house gas?
levels.closingAnswer: Hydrogen is not known as green house gas.

levels.question: The gas usually filled in the electric bulb is
levels.closingAnswer: The gas usually filled in the electric bulb is Nitrogen.
